===Etymology===
Dutch ''[[sloep]]'', from Middle Dutch ''slœpen'' (to glide).

===Noun===
'''sloop'''
# A single-masted [[sailboat]] with only one [[jib]].
# A sailing [[warship]], smaller than a [[frigate]], with its guns all on one [[deck]].

